### TaskTracker Stub – create sample feature for single-run agent testing
### 1. Start stub:  uv run python -m src.tasktracker.stub
### 2. Send this request; note the returned id (e.g. STUB-1)
### 3. Run agent:  uv run python -m src.main single-run --task-code STUB-1

@baseUrl = http://127.0.0.1:8765
@contentType = application/json

### Create sample feature (unit) – use returned id as --task-code in single-run
POST {{baseUrl}}/rest/api/unit/v2/test_case/create
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Accept: {{contentType}}

{
  "summary": "[New login] User can log in with email and password",
  "description": "Feature: New login flow. Steps: 1) Open login page, 2) Enter email and password, 3) Click Sign in. Expected: user is redirected to dashboard. Covers happy path for the new auth flow.",
  "suit": { "code": "test_case", "name": "Тест-кейс", "icon": "memo_pencil" },
  "space": { "code": "PVM", "name": "Пространство PVM" },
  "attributes": []
}

### Get all created tests (units in root folder)
POST {{baseUrl}}/extension/plugin/v2/rest/api/swtr_tms_plugin/v1/folder/hierarchy/TMS_test_case/units/filtered
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Accept: {{contentType}}

{
  "type": "TEST_CASE",
  "linkedTo": null,
  "unitFilters": { "page": { "page": 0, "size": 50 } }
}
